      "seed": 837714428,
      "version": 7,
      "versionNonce": 1930758340,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782804286900,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2) How do we achieve low latency (< 200ms) feed requests?",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2) How do we achieve low latency (< 200ms) feed requests?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "VwAXKID9j0wnfIpbfDSw_",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1579.0128215601057,
      "y": 6961.300763349642,
      "width": 1576.594970703125,
      "height": 280,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3D",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 590907076,
      "version": 138,
      "versionNonce": 132674172,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782804566482,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Good Sol: Sorted set(timestamp) Redis Cache with TTL\n- During cache expiration periods, all users requesting feeds for a region hit the database simultaneously, creating \n   thundering herd problems\n- users might not see new articles for up to 30 minutes\n\nBetter Sol: Realtime Cached Feeds with CDC \n- When new articles are published, CDC triggers immediately update the relevant regional caches without \n  waiting for TTL expiration.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Good Sol: Sorted set(timestamp) Redis Cache with TTL\n- During cache expiration periods, all users requesting feeds for a region hit the database simultaneously, creating \n   thundering herd problems\n- users might not see new articles for up to 30 minutes\n\nBetter Sol: Realtime Cached Feeds with CDC \n- When new articles are published, CDC triggers immediately update the relevant regional caches without \n  waiting for TTL expiration.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "JxAdF8Uo5_Nw1gppMK9So",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1568.5274060093157,
      "y": 7258.197789394882,
      "width": 1847.2987060546875,
      "height": 140,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3E",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1952519676,
      "version": 14,
      "versionNonce": 1318598596,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782804548573,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- When adding new articles, we use Redis ZADD to insert the article with its timestamp score, \n then immediately call ZREMRANGEBYRANK(Removes all elements in the sorted set stored at key with rank between start and stop.)\n with negative indices to remove the oldest articles beyond our limit. \n This ensures each regional cache stays at a manageable size while providing enough content for users to scroll through several pages.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- When adding new articles, we use Redis ZADD to insert the article with its timestamp score, \n then immediately call ZREMRANGEBYRANK(Removes all elements in the sorted set stored at key with rank between start and stop.)\n with negative indices to remove the oldest articles beyond our limit. \n This ensures each regional cache stays at a manageable size while providing enough content for users to scroll through several pages.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "w6s3B52D9NNpOaG1mb_KY",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1572.7585661149838,
      "y": 7424.401612944408,
      "width": 1817.507080078125,
      "height": 105,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3F",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1084182980,
      "version": 73,
      "versionNonce": 253263612,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782804551919,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- For feed requests, we simply read from the pre-computed Redis sorted sets using ZREVRANGE \n(Is a Redis command used to retrieve a specific range of members from a Sorted Set in descending order (highest score to lowest).)\n operations that complete in under 5ms",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- For feed requests, we simply read from the pre-computed Redis sorted sets using ZREVRANGE \n(Is a Redis command used to retrieve a specific range of members from a Sorted Set in descending order (highest score to lowest).)\n operations that complete in under 5ms",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "_pPxiGq4lh1SGl53Ofwd4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1625.195031793651,
      "y": 7628.766091188412,
      "width": 1549.3511962890625,
      "height": 1015,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3H",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1351439484,
      "version": 311,
      "versionNonce": 714228548,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782804930271,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "3) How do we ensure articles appear in feeds within 30 minutes of publication?\n\n- today's fast-paced news environment, a delay of several hours makes our news feed feel stale and irrelevant.\n\nGood Sol:\n- Increased RSS polling with Prioritizing polling with different intervals based on Collection Service (Publishers)\n\nBetter Sol:\n- Increased RSS polling + WebScraping( slower and less reliable than RSS parsing)\n\nBest Sol:\nPublisher Webhooks\n-  flips our model from pull-based to push-based by implementing webhooks where publishers notify us immediately \n  when they publish new content.\n\n- POST /webhooks/article-published\n    Your server has no way to know whether the request came from a trusted publisher or an attacker.\n    With a shared secret (most common)\n    When a publisher registers, you give them a secret key:\n    \n    POST /webhook/article-published\n    X-API-Key: abc123xyz\n    \n    {\n      \"title\": \"Election Results\",\n      \"link\": \"https://publisher.com/article/123\"\n    }\n\n-  primary limitation is that webhooks require coordination and buy-in from publishers.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "3) How do we ensure articles appear in feeds within 30 minutes of publication?\n\n- today's fast-paced news environment, a delay of several hours makes our news feed feel stale and irrelevant.\n\nGood Sol:\n- Increased RSS polling with Prioritizing polling with different intervals based on Collection Service (Publishers)\n\nBetter Sol:\n- Increased RSS polling + WebScraping( slower and less reliable than RSS parsing)\n\nBest Sol:\nPublisher Webhooks\n-  flips our model from pull-based to push-based by implementing webhooks where publishers notify us immediately \n  when they publish new content.\n\n- POST /webhooks/article-published\n    Your server has no way to know whether the request came from a trusted publisher or an attacker.\n    With a shared secret (most common)\n    When a publisher registers, you give them a secret key:\n    \n    POST /webhook/article-published\n    X-API-Key: abc123xyz\n    \n    {\n      \"title\": \"Election Results\",\n      \"link\": \"https://publisher.com/article/123\"\n    }\n\n-  primary limitation is that webhooks require coordination and buy-in from publishers.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "6Vq8fkgP7ub7KrbFzdXrS",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1610.7536878776234,
      "y": 8767.734140542398,
      "width": 862.2035522460938,
      "height": 70,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3I",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 498699260,
      "version": 81,
      "versionNonce": 1865652732,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782804996455,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "4) How do we handle media content (images/videos) efficiently?\n    - S3 + Cloudfront CDN with Multiple Sizes",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "4) How do we handle media content (images/videos) efficiently?\n    - S3 + Cloudfront CDN with Multiple Sizes",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "DANFcZIq3HsMslBgE5gcZ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1600.242157601675,
      "y": 8912.009469348117,
      "width": 1530.955078125,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
