      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782805235538,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "5) How do we handle traffic spikes during breaking news?\n- Feed Service (AutoScaling-> Horizontal Scaling)\n- DB have Caches\n- Redis Read Replicas\n- Most of our content would any way be region specific, so we need to scale region wise instead of global scale.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "5) How do we handle traffic spikes during breaking news?\n- Feed Service (AutoScaling-> Horizontal Scaling)\n- DB have Caches\n- Redis Read Replicas\n- Most of our content would any way be region specific, so we need to scale region wise instead of global scale.",
